Time Complexity:

Let n = size of array

    Single traversal → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Space Complexity:

    No extra data structures used

Overall: O(1)


Approach:

1. Initialize minDis = ∞ (Integer.MAX_VALUE)

2. Traverse the array:

   - If nums[i] == target:
     → Compute distance = |i - start|
     → Update minDis = min(minDis, distance)

3. After traversal:
   - Return minDis





class Solution {
    public int getMinDistance(int[] nums, int target, int start) {
        int minDis=Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            if(nums[i]==target) minDis = Math.min(minDis, (Math.abs(i-start)));
        }
        return minDis;
    }
}
